content_text:
I'd advise caution with $UMA. For sure at some point in the future the $3 price will take hold. But I inspected the transaction hashes, and most of the big-time pumps and dumps were from Binance itself. Not customers of Binance buying/selling through them, but Binance-owned wallets with special exchange designations.

It's pure and evil market manipulation. I can understand if it's just the market not agreeing with your sentiment, but when you're up against the exchange itself, there's no way to win. Do not get into coins that suddenly 40x their transaction volume in a single day (as what happened 6 days ago). The biggest whale playing with you might be Binance itself.
